comment: There seems to be a conflation between the sub-itinerary Sirmi-Treveros, which is the larger one, and another sub-sub-itinerary, Sirmi-Lauriaco, which ends sooner
Coordinates from Örberg, coming from Löhberg’s Index. Absent in Pleiades as far as I can see.

text_transcription: Item per ripam PANNONIAE a Daurono in GALLIS ad leg. XXX usque:
comment: This is in fact Laurino/Taurino. Again, unclear division. There seems to be an attempt at defining larger sub-itineraries upfront, but the language is unclear and there are other portions in the text
